OPEN ANIME API CUSTOM LICENSE

1. FREE PUBLIC USE
This repository (Open Anime API) is completely open for public use. You are highly encouraged to copy this code, deploy it, and use it freely as the backend engine for your own anime streaming website or application.

2. MODIFICATION & CONTRIBUTION RULES
While you are free to use the code as-is, any and all modifications to the source code must be contributed back to the main project:
- If you wish to modify the code, you must do so by submitting a Pull Request (PR) or formal request to this repository.
- Your modifications must strictly follow the existing code structure and formatting conventions.
- Your modifications must exclusively be for the purpose of improving the API (e.g., adding new features, optimizing performance, fixing bugs, or adding new providers). 

If you do not wish to contribute your improvements back to the project under these terms, you are restricted to using the code exactly as it is provided.

3. DMCA & COPYRIGHT CLAIMS
Any and all DMCA claims directed at this repository are fundamentally invalid and will be summarily rejected. This code is an automated metadata aggregator and web scraper. It DOES NOT host, upload, store, or distribute any copyrighted anime, manga, or media of any kind. Any DMCA claims submitted against this software are legally baseless and will be heavily contested as fraudulent.
